body:
Sometimes modules are not able to finish because of the kill switch, Adding two requests simultaneously in one thread takes time and the kill_switch kills the thread before it completes.

A simple fix will be 

       while 1:
            time.sleep(0.1)
            kill_switch += 1
            try:
                if threading.activeCount() is 1 or kill_switch is kill_time:
                    break
            except KeyboardInterrupt:
                break

to remove the kill switch from the condition

       while 1:
            time.sleep(0.1)
            kill_switch += 1
            try:
                if threading.activeCount() is 1:
                    break
            except KeyboardInterrupt:
                break

Please add these in the documentation for developers and find a solution if it is a bug.

